01:00.660 --> 01:02.218
Narrator:
After a generation of struggle

01:02.262 --> 01:04.126
changed the face of our nation,

01:04.164 --> 01:06.291
African Americans
entered the '70s

01:06.332 --> 01:08.163
with new found hope.

01:08.201 --> 01:09.896
- I am...
- I am...

01:09.936 --> 01:11.927
- Somebody!
- Somebody!

01:11.971 --> 01:13.370
Vibrant leaders emerged

01:13.406 --> 01:16.239
and black culture reached
its high point,

01:16.276 --> 01:17.709
influencing all facets
of American life.

01:18.144 --> 01:19.543
## Say it louder... ##

01:19.579 --> 01:21.570
Audience:
## I'm black and I'm proud ##

01:21.614 --> 01:23.479
Let me hear you...
## Say it louder... ##

01:23.516 --> 01:26.110
But progress slowed
in the decades that followed.

01:26.152 --> 01:28.712
Black culture began to lose
its distinctive flavor.

01:28.755 --> 01:30.848
(laughs)

01:30.890 --> 01:32.721
And as the millennium
drew to a close,

01:32.759 --> 01:34.522
disaster struck.

01:36.062 --> 01:39.031
These seemingly random events
were in fact orchestrated

01:39.065 --> 01:41.795
by The Man,
a villain obsessed

01:41.835 --> 01:44.827
with turning back the clock
on race relations.

01:44.871 --> 01:46.771
Just when it seemed
the funky spirit

01:46.806 --> 01:48.603
of the '70s
would be lost forever,

01:48.641 --> 01:52.236
a new hero emerged.
His name, Undercover Brother.

01:53.246 --> 01:56.181
