tear the roof off the mothersucka ##

02:00.954 --> 02:02.888
## Tear the roof off the sucka ##

02:02.922 --> 02:05.254
## Tear the roof off, we're gonna
tear the roof off the mothersucka ##

02:05.291 --> 02:07.452
## Tear the roof off the sucka ##

02:07.494 --> 02:10.429
## Tear the roof off, we're gonna
tear the roof off the mothersucka ##

02:10.463 --> 02:11.691
## Tear the roof off this sucka ##

02:11.731 --> 02:14.632
## You've got a real type
of thang going down ##

02:14.667 --> 02:16.294
## Getting down ##

02:16.336 --> 02:19.965
## There's a whole lot
of rhythm going round ##

02:20.006 --> 02:23.601
## Whoa! We want the funk ##

02:23.643 --> 02:27.374
## Give up the funk
Ah, we need the funk... ##

02:27.413 --> 02:30.382
Give it to me.
Need it, got to have it.

02:30.416 --> 02:32.475
- ## We need the funk ##
- We need the funk.

02:32.519 --> 02:34.783
- ## Gotta have the funk ##
- Say!

02:34.821 --> 02:37.153
## La-la-la-ya-ya ##

02:37.190 --> 02:41.149
## Do-do-do-do-do... ##

02:42.195 --> 02:44.629
(car honks)

02:44.664 --> 02:47.428
(tires screeching)

02:57.877 --> 03:00.368
## Turn this mother out... ##

03:03.149 --> 03:04.639
It ain't no thang.

03:05.818 --> 03:07.445
(together)
Yeah.

03:11.057 --> 03:13.287
A bird gonna shit
on my windshield?!

03:13.326 --> 03:14.953
Not on my Cadillac!

03:14.994 --> 03:17.986
I'm gonna chop your
feathers off
and put you in Chinatown!

03:18.031 --> 03:20.499
They gonna make
Peking Pigeon out of you!

03:20.533 --> 03:22.296
Damn!

03:22.535 --> 03:24.298
Unbeknownst
to Undercover Brother,

03:24.337 --> 03:27.033
there was a secret organization
dedicated to truth,

03:27.073 --> 03:29.268
justice,
and the Afro-American way.

03:29.309 --> 03:32.710
They had never crossed paths
until now.

03:49.529 --> 03:51.326
(beeping)

03:51.364 --> 03:52.831
Headquarters, come in.

03:52.865 --> 03:55.390
Good work, Sistah Girl.

03:55.435 --> 03:58.996
Data from the mainframe
ready to commence.

03:59.038 --> 04:02.007
- She's transmitting!
Are we up and ready?
- Yes, sir.

04:02.041 --> 04:04.202
And I've hacked into
the bank security system.

04:06.312 --> 04:07.870
Computer:
You've got soul.

04:07.914 --> 04:10.144
- We're in.
- Aha!

04:10.183 --> 04:14.279
The computer!
Another idea stolen from the black man.

04:14.320 --> 04:16.584
Did you all know that
George Washington Carver

04:16.623 --> 04:18.921
made the first computer
out of a peanut?

04:18.958 --> 04:20.322
- Hmm?
- A peanut?

04:20.360 --> 04:22.624
- A peanut!
- Shut up and get back to work!

04:22.662 --> 04:24.755
I've spent six months
setting up this operation

04:24.797 --> 04:26.526
and I want
to see everything...

04:26.566 --> 04:29.694
off-shore accounts,
dummy corporations, money laundering.

04:29.736 --> 04:32.102
If we can cut off his funds,

04:32.138 --> 04:34.436
we may finally be able
to stop The Man.

04:41.481 --> 04:44.450
Waited a long time for this.

04:46.152 --> 04:48.177
- What the hell?
- What the hell?

04:48.221 --> 04:50.917
- What the...
- Dissed.

04:50.957 --> 04:54.290
- Ah, solid.
- Hey!

04:54.327 --> 04:56.056
What the hell
are you doing, old man?

04:56.095 --> 04:58.086
(beeping)

05:07.173 --> 05:08.765
- AIl: Whoa!
- Headquarters...

05:08.808 --> 05:11.208
- Is there another
agent on this case?
- Hell, no!

05:11.244 --> 05:12.871
Damn it, who is that guy?

05:12.912 --> 05:15.972
I'll cross-reference the bank's
security camera with our database.

05:23.089 --> 05:25.148
Guard 1:
Come on, Uncle Ben!

05:26.192 --> 05:27.784
(together)
Whoa!

05:31.764 --> 05:33.959
Oh, shit!

05:34.000 --> 05:36.230
It's Macy Gray
with pork-chop sideburns!

05:37.904 --> 05:39.895
(karate yell)

05:41.174 --> 05:42.664
Who's bad?

05:46.479 --> 05:48.208
(screaming)

05:48.247 --> 05:51.114
Ohh! Right up
the pooper!

05:59.225 --> 06:01.955
- (Body & Soul music playing)
- Right on, sweet sistah.

06:04.731 --> 06:06.426
Chief:
Damn it, who is he?!

06:06.466 --> 06:09.458
- (exasperated sigh)
- Sistah Girl, abort mission!

06:12.805 --> 06:15.535
Damn it.
Who was that guy?

06:21.314 --> 06:25.444
## Hey, Undercover ##

06:25.485 --> 06:27.282
- ## Undercover Brother ##
- Solid.

06:29.989 --> 06:33.083
## Here's the plan...
he's got to fight the man ##

06:33.126 --> 06:35.993
## And he's looking fine
when he goes head to head ##

06:36.028 --> 06:39.464
- ## Dig those funky threads ##
- ## Wears his daddy's black
medallion ##

06:39.499 --> 06:41.126
## And it stands for pride ##

06:41.167 --> 06:44.193
## Truth and justice
be your guide ##

06:44.237 --> 06:47.229
- ## He's bad ##
- ## All he does is good ##

06:47.273 --> 06:49.264
## He's the Robin Hood
of the 'hood ##

06:49.308 --> 06:52.436
## Hey-hey, Undercover ##

06:52.478 --> 06:55.777
- Solid.
- ## Undercover Brother ##

06:55.815 --> 06:57.749
## Dressed to kill
in the Coupe Deville ##

06:57.784 --> 06:59.376
## Oh, hey! ##

06:59.419 --> 07:01.853
- ## Undercover ##
- Too funky for myself.

07:01.888 --> 07:05.654
- ## Undercover Brother ##
- ## Undercover Brother. ##

07:05.691 --> 07:07.124
Yeah.

07:33.519 --> 07:35.885
Announcer:
Mr. Feather, The Man wants to see you.

07:35.922 --> 07:37.651
Fabulous.

07:41.060 --> 07:43.961
Newscaster:
And now, the Channel 8 News
with Wendy Marshall

07:43.996 --> 07:45.327
and Chuck Marlboro.

07:45.364 --> 07:49.425
There's growing speculation
that former defense secretary and war
hero,

07:49.469 --> 07:51.994
General Warren Boutwell,
will run for President.

07:52.038 --> 07:54.506
He is considered
the first African-American

07:54.540 --> 07:56.132
with a legitimate chance
of winning.

07:56.175 --> 07:59.144
Wendy?
Yeah, he is a strong
candidate, Chuck.

07:59.178 --> 08:01.043
He's so well-spoken.
I've noticed that.

08:01.080 --> 08:04.243
General Boutwell seems to have
a lot of support all across the nation.

08:04.283 --> 08:06.444
Yes, and not just
in the urban areas.

08:06.486 --> 08:10.183
In fact, the decorated
four-star general and Vietnam vet

08:10.223 --> 08:12.020
is regarded
as one of the country's

08:12.058 --> 08:13.855
most well-respected
public figures.

08:13.893 --> 08:15.190
General:
Thank you very much.

08:15.228 --> 08:17.253
A staunch advocate
for civil rights,

08:17.296 --> 08:20.424
Boutwell has never backed down
from controversial issues.

08:20.466 --> 08:23.731
Indeed, if ever
there was a straighter
arrow
than Warren Boutwell,

08:23.769 --> 08:25.566
we'd be hard-pressed
to find him.

08:25.605 --> 08:27.766
Well, if he does declare
his candidacy,

08:27.807 --> 08:30.071
this certainly will be
an exciting race.

08:30.109 --> 08:33.044
Race? I'm not
touching that one.

08:33.078 --> 08:36.412
First, our children hip-hop
all over the suburbs.

08:36.448 --> 08:38.508
Now Boutwell
might be President?!

08:38.551 --> 08:42.681
They are taking over
every aspect of our culture!

08:42.722 --> 08:45.156
- Don't you agree,
Mr. Feather?
- Word.

08:45.191 --> 08:49.252
- For sheezy, my neezy.
- What did you say?

08:50.263 --> 08:51.958
I said... for sure.

08:51.998 --> 08:53.898
Yes, indeedy.

08:53.933 --> 08:55.958
(coughs)
I have a cold.

08:56.002 --> 08:59.233
I want the White House
to stay white.

08:59.272 --> 09:00.637
Eliminate him!

09:01.674 --> 09:03.767
But, sir,
if we kill him,

09:03.809 --> 09:06.403
we'll only be
making him a hero.

09:08.614 --> 09:10.411
Do you have a better idea?

09:10.449 --> 09:12.917
Our friends
at Multinational Inc.

09:12.952 --> 09:14.579
have been developing
a new drug

09:14.620 --> 09:17.214
with some very
interesting
side effects.

09:19.125 --> 09:22.561
I think we may have found
the perfect guinea pig.

09:33.973 --> 09:37.374
Newscaster:
The so called Afro Bandit
struck Multinational Bank.

09:37.410 --> 09:39.571
However, it appears
no money was stolen.

09:39.612 --> 09:42.706
Authorities questioned
singer Macy Gray,

09:42.748 --> 09:45.979
but she was released
for lack of evidence.

09:46.018 --> 09:48.111
Well, would anybody
like to explain exactly

09:48.154 --> 09:49.917
what the hell happened
at the bank?!

09:49.956 --> 09:52.254
His name
is Undercover Brother.

09:56.028 --> 09:58.019
Apparently, he was erasing
mortgage records

09:58.064 --> 10:00.624
so that low-income families
wouldn't lose their homes.

10:00.666 --> 10:01.758
Sistah Girl:
Great.

10:01.801 --> 10:04.736
A "Soul Train" reject
with a Robin Hood complex.

10:04.770 --> 10:07.295
- Now I've heard everything.
- Hey, hey, hey, now.

10:07.340 --> 10:09.171
At least he got
the job done.

10:09.208 --> 10:12.609
- That's the kind
of man we need around here.
- The keyword being "man"?

10:12.645 --> 10:14.408
Hold on.
I didn't say that, you did.

10:14.447 --> 10:16.142
Man-man.

10:16.182 --> 10:18.309
The General's
press conference is starting!

10:18.351 --> 10:20.012
Newscaster:
We interrupt this broadcast to take you live

10:20.052 --> 10:22.543
to a press conference
by General Warren Boutwell,

10:22.588 --> 10:23.987
in which he is expected
to announce

10:24.023 --> 10:27.151
that he is a candidate
for presidency of the United States.

10:27.193 --> 10:30.026
I wonder if he'll run
as a Democrat or an Independent.

10:30.062 --> 10:33.657
- Never know.
Might be a Republican.
- Oh, please.

10:33.699 --> 10:35.496
What kind
of self-respecting
black man

10:35.534 --> 10:37.001
would run
as a Republican?

10:37.036 --> 10:39.163
Name one thing
the Republican party

10:39.205 --> 10:41.070
has done
for black people. One!

10:41.107 --> 10:43.075
Well, they were
the party of Lincoln.

10:43.109 --> 10:44.838
They stood against
the tyranny of oppression

10:44.877 --> 10:46.538
by leading the call
for the Civil War,

10:46.579 --> 10:49.241
and forced passage
of the Emancipation Proclamation,

10:49.281 --> 10:50.543
which freed the slaves.

10:52.251 --> 10:54.151
All right,
name two things lately.

10:54.186 --> 10:56.154
Damn it, It doesn't matter
what party!

10:56.188 --> 10:58.748
This could be the first step
on the road to putting

10:58.791 --> 11:01.021
an African-American
in the White House.

11:01.060 --> 11:03.995
It's a great day
for black people of all races.

11:06.866 --> 11:09.699
- General: Good morning.
- Think about it!

11:09.735 --> 11:13.068
I've thought long and hard about how
I can best serve my country

11:13.105 --> 11:14.834
now that I'm no longer in uniform.

11:14.874 --> 11:17.001
Well, today...

11:17.043 --> 11:19.170
I am proud to announce

11:19.211 --> 11:21.042
that I will be...

11:21.080 --> 11:25.642
opening a chain
of fried chicken restaurants.

11:27.620 --> 11:29.952
AIl:
General Boutwell!

11:31.691 --> 11:33.022
Yes, sir.

11:33.059 --> 11:35.892
So, you're passing up a chance
to be President

11:35.928 --> 11:37.361
to open a chicken joint?

11:37.396 --> 11:40.422
A man like me doesn't have
any business in politics.

11:40.466 --> 11:42.900
They say you should
always do what you know.

11:42.935 --> 11:45.028
And what I know
is good fried chicken.

11:45.071 --> 11:47.005
- Ohh...
- General: Yes, ma'am.

11:47.039 --> 11:50.133
Don't you think your supporters
in the African-American community

11:50.176 --> 11:52.906
will be particularly disappointed?

11:52.945 --> 11:55.038
Not after they taste
the General's fried chicken.

11:55.081 --> 11:56.309
(gasps)

11:56.348 --> 11:58.714
General:
Surrender, Colonel,
here comes the General.

11:58.751 --> 12:01.151
- Will there be side dishes?
- Sweet potatoes...

12:01.187 --> 12:03.417
- (sighs)
- Black-eyed peas,

12:03.456 --> 12:06.619
- Mashed potatoes, macaroni...
- Mmm.

12:06.659 --> 12:09.184
cornbread,
and the General's special...

12:09.228 --> 12:11.924
hot sauce!

12:11.964 --> 12:14.228
(laughing)
That's all for today.

12:14.266 --> 12:16.359
Thank you very much.
Nice to see you all.

12:16.402 --> 12:18.734
Reporter:
General, what about desert?

12:22.675 --> 12:25.041
You know,
he does have a point
about that Colonel.

12:25.077 --> 12:26.567
I never trusted
the Colonel!

12:26.612 --> 12:29.479
Slaves cooked that chicken!
Ain't no white man know

12:29.515 --> 12:31.710
about no 16 herbs
and spices and giblets!

12:31.751 --> 12:33.912
Smart Brother,
if you so damn smart,

12:33.953 --> 12:36.945
- Why don't you explain
what just happened?
- (stammers)

12:36.989 --> 12:39.150
(mimics stammering)
If I wanted to hear something stupid,

12:39.191 --> 12:43.423
- I'd ask this skinny black ass!
- In your face!

12:43.462 --> 12:45.396
Skinny black... Hey!

12:45.431 --> 12:48.696
We got to find out exactly what happened
to the General, and fast!

12:48.734 --> 12:50.634
I'll get right on it.
Whoa, hold on.

12:50.669 --> 12:53.638
Not that fast. We need
some new blood on this case.

12:53.672 --> 12:57.005
What? Who? You can't just hire
some fool off the streets.

12:57.042 --> 13:00.011
Watch me.
Get me Undercover Brother!

13:00.713 --> 13:02.943
- (toilet flushing)
- Ooh, too funky for myself.

13:02.982 --> 13:04.006
Man on TV:
You were the only man
outside the palace.

13:05.151 --> 13:06.812
- I was outside.
- Jimmy!

13:06.852 --> 13:09.116
- But I wasn't the only one.
- Jim Kelly!

13:09.155 --> 13:12.750
- It is not possible.
- Watch out for the hand!
Watch out for the hand!

13:12.792 --> 13:14.453
(grunting)

13:14.493 --> 13:16.552
Gets you every time!
Spinning back-kick!

13:25.504 --> 13:27.972
(fake yawn)

13:28.007 --> 13:30.805
I think I'll lay down

13:30.843 --> 13:33.175
and get me a little bit
of sleep.

13:34.180 --> 13:36.011
(karate yell)

13:37.850 --> 13:39.841
Don't touch the hair!

13:43.088 --> 13:46.649
Okay, Bruce Leroy,
turn around.

13:46.692 --> 13:48.523
Slowly.

13:51.864 --> 13:54.059
If you gonna shoot me,

13:54.099 --> 13:55.623
shoot me.

14:03.309 --> 14:05.300
Thank you, Jesus.

14:07.613 --> 14:09.103
Hmm.

14:11.984 --> 14:13.474
Dig it.

14:13.519 --> 14:16.147
You that Sistah Girl
from the bank, huh?

14:17.990 --> 14:20.083
I guess you like
what you saw earlier.

14:20.826 --> 14:23.260
Look, baby,
let's stop fooling
around.

14:23.295 --> 14:25.092
Your body's slammin',
let's get to jammin'.

14:25.297 --> 14:26.628
Excuse me?

14:26.665 --> 14:29.964
Oh, nothing relaxes a brother
after a hard day of going
undercover

14:30.002 --> 14:31.833
like a little piece of the cookie.

14:33.005 --> 14:35.997
Goddamn.
My cookie would
break you in half.

14:36.041 --> 14:40.671
Maybe, but that would be
some long division.

14:42.181 --> 14:43.512
Long.

14:44.516 --> 14:46.984
You hit me pretty good,
but I wasn't ready.

14:47.019 --> 14:50.682
Now, any time you think
you want to get feisty
or throw down...

14:51.857 --> 14:54.018
(crash)

14:55.194 --> 14:56.991
So, Sistah Girl,

14:57.029 --> 14:59.497
if you're not here
for Undercover Lover,

14:59.531 --> 15:01.624
you must be here
for Undercover Brother.

15:01.667 --> 15:03.931
What, pray tell,
can I do for you today?

15:05.437 --> 15:07.769
Sistah Girl:
Okay, we're here. Now be cool.

15:07.806 --> 15:10.104
- This place is top secret.
- Undercover Brother: Solid.

15:11.310 --> 15:12.971
Man:
Man, you know you ain't right.

15:13.012 --> 15:15.344
Whoo-oo!

15:15.381 --> 15:17.246
I'm gonna need
my custom shears

15:17.283 --> 15:18.614
for this masterpiece.

15:18.651 --> 15:21.484
Careful. Puncture him
and the hot air's liable to kill you.

15:21.520 --> 15:23.351
- Sistah Girl: Take a seat.
- Don't mind if I do.

15:23.856 --> 15:27.121
- We're gonna hook you right up.
- Holy funkadelic!

15:27.159 --> 15:29.127
This is some kind

15:29.161 --> 15:31.459
of secret organization
you have here.

15:31.864 --> 15:33.855
Look at all this hi-tech
spy equipment.

15:33.899 --> 15:37.926
You got clippers,
you got T.C.B. activator.

15:37.970 --> 15:40.996
I mean, your only competition
must be the K.G.B.

15:41.807 --> 15:43.672
- (laughter)
- Or the F.B.I.

15:48.013 --> 15:49.844
(screaming)

15:52.785 --> 15:55.811
Who the hell are you, woman?
You're the Grim Reaper!

15:55.854 --> 15:57.344
I don't want to go to hell!

15:57.389 --> 15:59.289
I ain't never did
nothing but good!

15:59.325 --> 16:01.657
I swear to God
I ain't done nothing wrong!

16:03.395 --> 16:05.454
(screaming continues)

16:10.469 --> 16:12.266
Oh, come on.

16:12.304 --> 16:15.796
The flashing light and fan
make the drop seem worse than it is.

16:20.980 --> 16:23.141
I knew that.
Mm-hmm.

16:25.484 --> 16:27.952
Computerized voice:
Entering secure area.

16:27.987 --> 16:29.955
Stand here.

16:29.989 --> 16:31.980
Right here?

16:51.844 --> 16:55.405
Computer:
Blackness confirmed. You got soul.

16:55.447 --> 16:57.244
What I'm about to show you

16:57.282 --> 16:59.273
few people have ever seen before.

17:01.253 --> 17:04.654
P. A:
Would Agent Jefferson please pick up
the black courtesy phone?

17:08.460 --> 17:10.758
Agents report
to the ready room.

17:10.796 --> 17:12.787
Agents report
to the ready room.

17:14.465 --> 17:16.763
Welcome
to the Brotherhood.

17:16.801 --> 17:18.633
Solid.

17:20.806 --> 17:22.603
Yes, I know.

17:22.641 --> 17:25.666
I really don't want to talk about this
over the telephone.

17:25.711 --> 17:28.042
Perhaps we could meet
at a secret location?

17:28.079 --> 17:30.708
Okay. No, that sounds great.

17:30.749 --> 17:33.240
All right. Revolution.
Take care.

17:33.285 --> 17:35.219
Man:
